translated: Boräng, Sven Gunnar, high school teacher, Västervik, b. 11/6/1903 in Alboga, Älvsborg County. Married in 1935 to the school teacher Britta Norman with a Master's degree. Children: Egil b. 1940, Kerstin b. 1942, Kajsa b. 1944, Gunnar b. 1947. Studied in Lund, passed exam in 1925, received a Master's degree in 1932, and trained as a teacher in 1933. Worked as substitute teacher in Svedala and Vellinge in 1933, then served as substitute high school teacher in Enköping in 1933 and high school teacher of Swedish language and gymnastics in Haapsalu, Estonia from 1934-1938. Became a seminar assistant in Haparanda from 1938-1939, then a trainee at Vasa high school in Gothenburg from 1939-1940. Worked as high school teacher in Hallsberg in 1940, in Lidköping in 1941, and as a biology teacher focusing on health and chemistry at Västervik high school since 1941. Inspector at the Västervik teaching institution for students with intellectual disabilities, a scout leader, and authored several publications including "On the construction of the brain of Athena noctua" (1933), "Ornithological notes from Haapsalu" (1936), and "Discovery of two mayflies (Ephemeroptera) in Estonia" (1937), as well as contributed to the Estonian-Swedish magazine Kustbon. Translated and analyzed Estonian articles for an old journal.
